    <p class="section-intro section-intro--light">Every vote I cast on Council will be guided by these commitments — and I'll explain my reasoning publicly, every time.</p>
    <div class="priorities-grid">
      <a class="priority-card" href="/priorities/fiscal/">
        <div class="priority-card-icon">💰</div>
        <h3>Fiscal Responsibility</h3>
        <p>Taxpayer money is trust. I'll ask hard questions before any major expenditure, push for competitive procurement, and ensure Council understands what it's approving.</p>
        <span class="priority-card-link">Three documented cases →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="priority-card" href="/priorities/community-services/">
        <div class="priority-card-icon">🏊</div>
        <h3>Community Services &amp; Recreation</h3>
        <p>A $4.8M facilities gap with no reserve, no plan, no timeline. The township's own Asset Management Plan identifies it. We need to start planning now.</p>
        <span class="priority-card-link">The $4.8M question →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="priority-card" href="/priorities/communication/">
        <div class="priority-card-icon">📡</div>
        <h3>Communication &amp; Technology</h3>
        <p>Residents shouldn't have to dig for information about their government. I built the tools that prove it's possible — now I'll make them the standard.</p>
        <span class="priority-card-link">The 13-point plan →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="priority-card" href="/priorities/governance/">
        <div class="priority-card-icon">⚖️</div>
